1
00:00:15,100 --> 00:00:18,800
Excuse me, we have a warrant
of arrest for Mrs. Rina Ramos.

2
00:00:18,933 --> 00:00:20,200
- Why?
- For two counts

3
00:00:20,333 --> 00:00:22,700
of frustrated murder
against Mrs. Amanda Madrigal

4
00:00:22,833 --> 00:00:24,567
and Miss Eden Sta. Maria.

5
00:00:24,700 --> 00:00:26,333
Are you happy now?

6
00:00:26,467 --> 00:00:28,767
Whatever is going on
with your life,

7
00:00:28,900 --> 00:00:31,000
you've done it to yourself.

8
00:00:31,133 --> 00:00:33,933
I didn't come here
to pick a fight with you.

9
00:00:34,100 --> 00:00:37,500
I'm here to usher you
to the hell you've chosen.

10
00:00:37,633 --> 00:00:39,433
Red, I thought
I wouldn't see you again

11
00:00:39,567 --> 00:00:40,900
after the accident.

12
00:00:41,033 --> 00:00:43,067
I thought that was the end
of everything.

13
00:00:43,200 --> 00:00:44,933
That will never happen.

14
00:00:45,067 --> 00:00:46,700
We survived the island.

15
00:00:46,833 --> 00:00:48,867
We survived our family's feud.

16
00:00:49,000 --> 00:00:50,800
Nothing can separate us now.

17
00:00:50,933 --> 00:00:52,767
I want to ask
for your forgiveness.

18
00:00:52,900 --> 00:00:54,667
I didn't realize
how much you love my daughter.

19
00:00:54,800 --> 00:00:56,167
Thank you, Amanda.

20
00:00:56,300 --> 00:01:00,433
Accepting my relationship
with Yenyen is enough.

21
00:01:00,567 --> 00:01:03,300
The court's decision
will be released tomorrow.

22
00:01:03,433 --> 00:01:05,900
Please, do something for them
to get me acquitted.

23
00:01:06,033 --> 00:01:09,333
If I do that, it's like turning
a blind eye to your misdeed.

24
00:01:09,500 --> 00:01:10,967
I did it for you
and your brother.

25
00:01:11,100 --> 00:01:13,000
That's why I'm having
a hard time, Mom!

26
00:01:13,133 --> 00:01:14,433
I know you did this

27
00:01:14,567 --> 00:01:16,867
because of your love
for my brother and me.

28
00:01:17,000 --> 00:01:17,967
How is Red doing?

29
00:01:18,100 --> 00:01:20,333
How is he taking
Rina's circumstances?

30
00:01:20,467 --> 00:01:23,200
I know he's having a hard time.

31
00:01:23,333 --> 00:01:24,767
He loves his mom.

32
00:01:24,900 --> 00:01:27,000
Should I drop the case
against her?

33
00:01:27,133 --> 00:01:31,900
No. Rina has to learn
her lesson.

34
00:01:32,033 --> 00:01:34,467
You have to pay for your sin.

35
00:01:34,600 --> 00:01:38,700
It hurts to hear that
you're abandoning me, too, Red.

36
00:01:38,833 --> 00:01:39,667
Why?

37
00:01:39,800 --> 00:01:41,367
- I can't do anything.
- Red.

38
00:01:41,533 --> 00:01:42,900
Red.

39
00:01:43,033 --> 00:01:44,033
Red,

40
00:01:44,167 --> 00:01:45,233
please, Red.

41
00:01:45,367 --> 00:01:48,667
Please, I didn't raise you
so you can abandon me.

42
00:01:48,800 --> 00:01:50,967
Please, don't leave me, Red.

43
00:01:51,100 --> 00:01:54,200
Red, help me.

44
00:01:55,233 --> 00:01:57,733
Red. Help me.

45
00:02:03,733 --> 00:02:04,567
Ma'am.

46
00:02:04,700 --> 00:02:06,900
Mr. Akashi wants you
to have this.

47
00:02:07,033 --> 00:02:10,100
I can't miss your wedding, Son.

48
00:02:11,567 --> 00:02:19,267
That's why I've prepared
a big surprise for you.

49
00:02:21,433 --> 00:02:23,300
She said she had a surprise
for us.

50
00:02:23,433 --> 00:02:25,133
I know she won't leave us alone.

51
00:02:25,267 --> 00:02:26,433
She's going to make a scene.

52
00:02:26,567 --> 00:02:28,367
We have to stop her, Red.

53
00:02:28,500 --> 00:02:30,633
I promise you,
my mom can't hurt us.

54
00:02:30,767 --> 00:02:33,500
No member of my family
will get hurt, I promise.

55
00:02:33,633 --> 00:02:34,833
She can't harm you.

56
00:02:39,933 --> 00:02:40,900
Thanks.

57
00:02:45,333 --> 00:02:46,900
I already called dad.

58
00:02:47,033 --> 00:02:49,533
I told him we needed
to tighten the security.

59
00:02:49,700 --> 00:02:51,867
I told him about what you saw.

60
00:02:52,000 --> 00:02:53,967
He's going to report it
to the police.

61
00:02:54,100 --> 00:02:55,367
Everything is okay.

62
00:02:55,500 --> 00:02:57,067
I'm scared, Red.

63
00:02:58,667 --> 00:03:01,100
As long as she's out there,

64
00:03:01,233 --> 00:03:03,667
I still worry
about what she can do.

65
00:03:05,200 --> 00:03:06,700
Yen.

66
00:03:06,833 --> 00:03:09,167
My mom can't harm us anymore.

67
00:03:09,300 --> 00:03:11,733
She won't be able to find us,
okay?

68
00:03:11,867 --> 00:03:14,000
What surprise
is she talking about?

69
00:03:15,167 --> 00:03:17,267
Nothing. Maybe she's just
messing with your head.

70
00:03:17,400 --> 00:03:19,667
She has nothing against us.

71
00:03:21,067 --> 00:03:21,767
Yen, come on.

72
00:03:21,900 --> 00:03:23,233
It's our special day.

73
00:03:23,367 --> 00:03:25,467
Are you going
to let her ruin our day?

74
00:03:27,733 --> 00:03:29,100
You should get ready.

75
00:03:29,233 --> 00:03:30,233
Okay?

76
00:03:31,667 --> 00:03:32,667
Go on.

77
00:03:32,800 --> 00:03:34,667
I'm not supposed to see you
before our wedding.

78
00:03:34,800 --> 00:03:35,767
Come on.

79
00:03:35,900 --> 00:03:36,833
Okay.

80
00:03:53,300 --> 00:03:56,500
Isn't that a bad omen?

81
00:03:58,167 --> 00:03:59,500
I don't know.

82
00:03:59,633 --> 00:04:01,700
I don't really believe
in those stuff.

83
00:04:02,767 --> 00:04:04,367
But one thing is for sure.

84
00:04:05,400 --> 00:04:07,433
If Aunt Rina's here,

85
00:04:09,500 --> 00:04:11,000
maybe you're in danger.

86
00:04:15,033 --> 00:04:15,933
Whatever.

87
00:04:16,067 --> 00:04:17,367
Why do you have to speak
in English?

88
00:04:25,400 --> 00:04:27,300
My gosh! It's a winner!

89
00:04:27,467 --> 00:04:28,933
It's gorgeous!

90
00:04:29,067 --> 00:04:30,167
Oh my god, Amanda.

91
00:04:30,300 --> 00:04:32,667
Eden, you're so gorgeous.

92
00:04:32,800 --> 00:04:34,933
- Mom.
- You know what makes you

93
00:04:35,067 --> 00:04:39,333
more beautiful?
It's the happiness in your eyes.

94
00:04:39,467 --> 00:04:41,033
Thank you, Mom.

95
00:04:41,167 --> 00:04:43,233
After everything
we've been through,

96
00:04:43,367 --> 00:04:46,433
all I want is to be a part
of your good life.

97
00:04:49,400 --> 00:04:51,067
So gorgeous.

98
00:04:51,200 --> 00:04:52,867
I take after you, Mom.

99
00:04:53,000 --> 00:04:55,033
My gosh. I can't get over it.

100
00:04:55,167 --> 00:04:56,600
This is it!

101
00:04:59,800 --> 00:05:01,100
Red is waiting.

102
00:05:01,267 --> 00:05:02,300
The wedding is about to start.

103
00:05:03,567 --> 00:05:07,100
Finally, one of my dreams
is about to come true.

104
00:05:08,133 --> 00:05:11,000
Too bad our child is gone now.

105
00:05:12,200 --> 00:05:13,600
I wish she was here right now.

106
00:05:15,800 --> 00:05:17,200
Let's just be grateful

107
00:05:17,333 --> 00:05:19,167
that you and Red
are still alive.

108
00:05:20,233 --> 00:05:22,167
You can still make more babies.

109
00:05:22,300 --> 00:05:23,767
You can build a family.

110
00:05:23,900 --> 00:05:25,967
Right? You two are still young.

111
00:05:30,233 --> 00:05:34,000
Son, I want to congratulate you.

112
00:05:34,167 --> 00:05:35,733
Even though your mom
is not here,

113
00:05:35,867 --> 00:05:39,167
I wish you nothing
but happiness.

114
00:05:39,300 --> 00:05:40,300
Thanks, Dad.

115
00:05:47,267 --> 00:05:48,333
I'm back!

116
00:05:49,900 --> 00:05:53,233
Did you really think I'll just
let myself rot in jail?

117
00:05:53,367 --> 00:05:54,900
No!

118
00:05:55,033 --> 00:05:56,933
You can't take me down!

119
00:06:02,533 --> 00:06:03,400
Eden!
Eden!

120
00:06:04,533 --> 00:06:05,933
- Eden!
- Raichu!

121
00:06:06,067 --> 00:06:08,200
- You have to see this.
- What?

122
00:06:08,367 --> 00:06:08,733
Hurry!

123
00:06:08,867 --> 00:06:10,033
What's going on?

124
00:06:10,167 --> 00:06:11,367
- Come on, let's go.
- Come on.

125
00:06:13,133 --> 00:06:18,200
I know this day
is very special for you, Red.

126
00:06:18,333 --> 00:06:22,333
Isn't today your wedding day?

127
00:06:22,467 --> 00:06:23,600
Right?

128
00:06:23,733 --> 00:06:27,167
Do you think
I wouldn't send my regards?

129
00:06:28,867 --> 00:06:32,833
This video message is perfect
for the two of you.

130
00:06:34,767 --> 00:06:41,067
Because you can't handle
the advanced wedding gift

131
00:06:41,233 --> 00:06:42,433
that I prepared for both of you.

132
00:06:43,400 --> 00:06:44,500
Are you ready?

133
00:06:48,067 --> 00:06:51,100
I just want to say that...

134
00:06:52,900 --> 00:06:55,267
Red, Eden,

135
00:06:56,933 --> 00:06:59,267
your child is not dead.

136
00:07:00,267 --> 00:07:01,600
Yes, you heard me right.

137
00:07:01,733 --> 00:07:03,600
Your child is not dead.

138
00:07:03,733 --> 00:07:08,000
In fact, she is very much alive.

139
00:07:10,067 --> 00:07:11,867
I just made you think
the baby's dead

140
00:07:12,000 --> 00:07:13,700
because I want to ruin
your relationship.

141
00:07:14,733 --> 00:07:16,167
And...

142
00:07:17,233 --> 00:07:19,000
I know where she is.

143
00:07:20,500 --> 00:07:21,667
I know.

144
00:07:23,267 --> 00:07:25,500
Our child is alive!

145
00:07:25,633 --> 00:07:26,800
The child is alive.

146
00:07:26,933 --> 00:07:30,567
And I know where she is.

147
00:07:32,800 --> 00:07:37,433
So good luck with your new life!

148
00:07:37,567 --> 00:07:39,533
Or should I say...

149
00:07:40,733 --> 00:07:43,733
to the hell
that's waiting for you!

150
00:07:43,867 --> 00:07:46,167
Because this is not over yet.

151
00:07:46,300 --> 00:07:50,433
I will have the last laugh!

152
00:07:54,867 --> 00:07:56,233
Bye!

153
00:07:58,167 --> 00:07:59,133
Our child is alive, Red.

154
00:07:59,267 --> 00:08:00,700
Did you hear what she said?

155
00:08:00,833 --> 00:08:02,467
She knows where Baby Chloe is.

156
00:08:05,100 --> 00:08:06,667
What happened to Rina?

157
00:08:06,800 --> 00:08:07,933
She's out of her mind!

158
00:08:09,300 --> 00:08:11,967
She could be making this up
because she hates us.

159
00:08:12,100 --> 00:08:14,233
She could be lying.

160
00:08:14,367 --> 00:08:15,400
Okay, thank you.

161
00:08:16,967 --> 00:08:18,700
I called the precinct.

162
00:08:18,833 --> 00:08:20,500
Rina escaped!

163
00:08:20,633 --> 00:08:22,300
I knew it! She won't stop!

164
00:08:22,467 --> 00:08:24,567
She won't leave us alone!

165
00:08:24,700 --> 00:08:29,633
Now she's using your child's
memory to hurt all of us.

166
00:08:32,167 --> 00:08:33,900
At this point,

167
00:08:34,033 --> 00:08:35,867
she will do anything

168
00:08:36,000 --> 00:08:37,067
to get revenge.

169
00:08:37,200 --> 00:08:38,200
So what are we going to do?

170
00:08:38,333 --> 00:08:39,367
Won't we believe her?

171
00:08:39,500 --> 00:08:41,267
And then she'll use
some random kid as bait!

172
00:08:41,400 --> 00:08:43,700
Are we just going
to shrug it off?

173
00:08:43,833 --> 00:08:46,500
We can't be sure
if it really is their child.

174
00:08:48,900 --> 00:08:50,567
What if she's telling the truth?

175
00:08:50,700 --> 00:08:53,733
What if she's not lying?

176
00:08:53,900 --> 00:08:56,567
What if we can still get
our child back, Red?

177
00:08:56,700 --> 00:08:57,733
And be with her?

178
00:09:08,000 --> 00:09:10,233
I remember
being in the car with them.

179
00:09:10,367 --> 00:09:11,733
And...

180
00:09:11,867 --> 00:09:13,300
I was in severe pain.

181
00:09:13,433 --> 00:09:15,167
And then...

182
00:09:15,467 --> 00:09:16,467
Mommy Rina was there.

183
00:09:16,600 --> 00:09:17,767
She was taking care of me.

184
00:09:17,900 --> 00:09:19,000
It hurts so much!

185
00:09:19,133 --> 00:09:20,733
- I can't bear the pain anymore!
- Hang in there, Eden.

186
00:09:20,867 --> 00:09:21,967
We're almost there.

187
00:09:22,100 --> 00:09:23,500
Hurry up, Zandro!

188
00:09:23,633 --> 00:09:25,633
I'm driving as fast as I can!

189
00:09:25,967 --> 00:09:27,767
Uncle Zandro was driving!

190
00:09:29,700 --> 00:09:30,700
Rina, we have a problem!

191
00:09:30,833 --> 00:09:32,500
Problem? What's the problem?

192
00:09:32,633 --> 00:09:33,833
The brake is not working!

193
00:09:33,967 --> 00:09:35,933
- What?
- What? Do something about it!

194
00:09:36,067 --> 00:09:37,733
Zandro, do something!

195
00:09:37,867 --> 00:09:39,233
I will!

196
00:09:42,567 --> 00:09:44,133
And then we had an accident.

197
00:09:45,800 --> 00:09:47,000
I think we crashed into a tree.

198
00:09:47,133 --> 00:09:48,600
I'm not sure.

199
00:09:48,733 --> 00:09:50,400
When I woke up,

200
00:09:50,533 --> 00:09:52,267
there was a midwife.

201
00:09:52,400 --> 00:09:54,900
She helped me give birth.

202
00:09:55,033 --> 00:09:57,100
Someone will help us out.

203
00:09:57,233 --> 00:09:59,500
You have to give birth
to your baby.

204
00:09:59,633 --> 00:10:00,533
Push!

205
00:10:00,700 --> 00:10:02,533
I can see the baby's head now!

206
00:10:02,667 --> 00:10:03,600
Come on, come on, Eden.

207
00:10:03,733 --> 00:10:05,467
Push! You have to push!

208
00:10:05,600 --> 00:10:07,233
Come on. There it is.

209
00:10:07,367 --> 00:10:08,767
Your baby's coming.

210
00:10:08,900 --> 00:10:10,233
One more time. There it is.

211
00:10:10,367 --> 00:10:11,767
Push, push! Come on!

212
00:10:19,233 --> 00:10:21,700
Then I heard baby Chloe's cry.

213
00:10:23,833 --> 00:10:25,467
But I didn't get to hold her.

214
00:10:29,200 --> 00:10:31,433
And then I felt so weak.

215
00:10:31,567 --> 00:10:32,700
I fell asleep.

216
00:10:34,033 --> 00:10:35,600
I should have held on.

217
00:10:39,500 --> 00:10:44,567
Eden, you did everything
you could to save your baby.

218
00:10:45,967 --> 00:10:48,467
When I woke up,
my baby was gone.

219
00:10:48,600 --> 00:10:50,467
Our baby, Red.

220
00:10:50,600 --> 00:10:53,000
Mommy Rina told me
that she had stopped breathing.

221
00:10:54,733 --> 00:10:55,967
Eden.

222
00:10:56,100 --> 00:10:58,467
Auntie, where's my baby?

223
00:10:58,600 --> 00:11:00,133
She's gone.

224
00:11:00,267 --> 00:11:02,000
She's dead.

225
00:11:02,133 --> 00:11:03,533
That's not true!

226
00:11:03,667 --> 00:11:04,833
- She's dead.
- You're lying!

227
00:11:04,967 --> 00:11:06,100
I heard her cry!

228
00:11:06,233 --> 00:11:07,733
- Let me see my baby!
- She's gone!

229
00:11:07,900 --> 00:11:09,100
The baby's gone!

230
00:11:09,233 --> 00:11:11,300
She's gone!

231
00:11:11,433 --> 00:11:14,033
Where is my baby?

232
00:11:14,167 --> 00:11:15,467
She's gone, Eden.

233
00:11:16,867 --> 00:11:18,667
But I didn't believe her.

234
00:11:20,333 --> 00:11:21,733
Because even if we buried her,

235
00:11:21,867 --> 00:11:25,233
I could feel
she was still alive.

236
00:11:25,367 --> 00:11:26,867
Red, I told you about that
before, remember?

237
00:11:28,467 --> 00:11:29,567
You couldn't explain it,

238
00:11:29,700 --> 00:11:32,467
but you said you could feel
that our baby was still alive.

239
00:11:34,600 --> 00:11:35,567
Maybe....

240
00:11:37,200 --> 00:11:39,367
She can still be alive.

241
00:11:39,500 --> 00:11:41,133
Our baby may still be alive.

242
00:11:42,567 --> 00:11:44,400
Maybe my mom took her away

243
00:11:44,533 --> 00:11:48,233
because she wanted
to separate us.

244
00:11:48,367 --> 00:11:53,433
You rushed into things.

245
00:11:53,567 --> 00:11:56,567
You didn't know each other
that well yet.

246
00:11:56,700 --> 00:11:57,700
But look at what happened.

247
00:11:57,833 --> 00:12:00,233
You guys got pregnant,
so what else can we do?

248
00:12:00,367 --> 00:12:04,767
You two have no good foundation
for your relationship.

249
00:12:04,900 --> 00:12:06,500
Rina.

250
00:12:06,633 --> 00:12:10,100
Somebody has to speak
the truth here.

251
00:12:10,233 --> 00:12:13,733
You two are together
because of the baby, right?

252
00:12:13,867 --> 00:12:15,067
And now that the baby's gone...

253
00:12:16,133 --> 00:12:20,133
maybe it's time for you guys
to rethink your relationship.

254
00:12:21,400 --> 00:12:22,400
I think...

255
00:12:23,567 --> 00:12:24,800
the two of you are no longer
happy with each other.

256
00:12:26,767 --> 00:12:28,067
We have to get her back, Red.

257
00:12:28,200 --> 00:12:29,700
We have to get our baby back!

258
00:12:35,900 --> 00:12:39,267
Only one person can confirm
if Rina's telling the truth.

259
00:12:41,400 --> 00:12:44,067
And that's if he's going
to talk.

260
00:13:15,167 --> 00:13:16,600
Yen, why don't you
sit down first?

261
00:13:18,067 --> 00:13:19,033
I can't sit still, Red.

262
00:13:19,167 --> 00:13:20,533
I have so much on my mind.

263
00:13:22,133 --> 00:13:23,767
I'm so emotional.

264
00:13:32,467 --> 00:13:34,833
Red, what if Uncle Zandro
won't talk?

265
00:13:35,967 --> 00:13:38,333
You know
he doesn't care about us.

266
00:13:39,567 --> 00:13:42,567
I feel like he will take
Mommy Rina's side until the end.

267
00:13:48,133 --> 00:13:49,133
Red.

268
00:14:03,667 --> 00:14:04,767
Red, what's wrong?

269
00:14:08,767 --> 00:14:09,833
I'm sorry.

270
00:14:11,833 --> 00:14:13,000
I'm really sorry, Yen.

271
00:14:14,000 --> 00:14:15,967
It's not your fault.

272
00:14:16,100 --> 00:14:17,067
We didn't do anything wrong.

273
00:14:17,200 --> 00:14:18,533
We were just caught
in their feud.

274
00:14:19,600 --> 00:14:21,033
And no matter what happens,

275
00:14:23,467 --> 00:14:25,500
I don't regret loving you.

276
00:14:27,633 --> 00:14:29,433
We've been through
a lot together, Red.

277
00:14:30,967 --> 00:14:32,667
We'll overcome this too.

278
00:14:34,000 --> 00:14:37,900
And we'll find out the truth.

279
00:15:11,033 --> 00:15:14,400
So, are you now
one big happy family?

280
00:15:16,333 --> 00:15:18,633
You came here empty-handed.

281
00:15:18,767 --> 00:15:20,767
Come on, Red.

282
00:15:20,900 --> 00:15:22,167
This is not how things work.

283
00:15:22,300 --> 00:15:24,800
We need something from you.

284
00:15:24,933 --> 00:15:25,967
From me?

285
00:15:27,133 --> 00:15:28,300
Me?

286
00:15:28,433 --> 00:15:30,233
Tell us the truth.

287
00:15:30,367 --> 00:15:31,800
Is our baby still alive?

288
00:15:36,100 --> 00:15:37,533
Uncle Zandro, please.

289
00:15:39,233 --> 00:15:41,400
I don't know
what you're talking about.

290
00:15:41,533 --> 00:15:47,167
Rina told us
the baby was still alive.

291
00:15:47,300 --> 00:15:49,133
Really?

292
00:15:49,267 --> 00:15:51,567
So Rina told you already.

293
00:15:51,700 --> 00:15:52,800
Why are you here then?

294
00:15:53,800 --> 00:15:55,100
You bastard!

295
00:15:59,967 --> 00:16:01,700
Tell us the truth, Zandro.

296
00:16:01,833 --> 00:16:04,133
We're talking
about a baby's life here.

297
00:16:04,267 --> 00:16:06,467
Have a little conscience.

298
00:16:06,600 --> 00:16:08,400
Have mercy on their child.

299
00:16:08,567 --> 00:16:10,200
Why should I feel bad?

300
00:16:10,333 --> 00:16:12,533
They're the reason
I'm here right now!

301
00:16:13,933 --> 00:16:15,700
You ruined our plans!

302
00:16:15,833 --> 00:16:18,333
For what? For love?

303
00:16:18,467 --> 00:16:21,700
We never did anything wrong
to you.

304
00:16:21,833 --> 00:16:24,633
Please, keep our child
out of it.

305
00:16:26,500 --> 00:16:28,000
You know...

306
00:16:28,133 --> 00:16:30,300
you should ask my sister.

307
00:16:30,433 --> 00:16:32,800
Because no matter
where your child is...

308
00:16:32,933 --> 00:16:34,667
whether she's dead or alive...

309
00:16:34,800 --> 00:16:36,100
whether she's in heaven or hell,

310
00:16:36,233 --> 00:16:38,833
wherever that baby is,
I don't give a darn!

311
00:16:38,967 --> 00:16:40,433
Monster!

312
00:16:40,567 --> 00:16:41,967
Dad!

313
00:16:42,133 --> 00:16:42,933
Sir, that's enough !

314
00:16:44,267 --> 00:16:45,200
- Sir, that's enough!
- Dad!

315
00:16:45,333 --> 00:16:46,633
Lucho! Lucho!

316
00:17:01,567 --> 00:17:02,833
Stop it!

317
00:17:02,967 --> 00:17:05,567
You two have to stop!

318
00:17:05,700 --> 00:17:06,967
Come on! Victor!

319
00:17:07,100 --> 00:17:08,067
That's enough!

320
00:17:10,967 --> 00:17:11,867
Lucho!

321
00:17:12,000 --> 00:17:13,600
Victor!

322
00:17:13,733 --> 00:17:15,567
Come here, both of you!

323
00:17:18,867 --> 00:17:19,733
Wait!

324
00:17:19,867 --> 00:17:21,033
Wait,

325
00:17:21,167 --> 00:17:22,733
we're not done talking yet.

326
00:17:24,300 --> 00:17:25,900
I have nothing else to tell you.

327
00:17:26,033 --> 00:17:27,100
Uncle Zandro,

328
00:17:28,133 --> 00:17:29,300
I know you were only mad.

329
00:17:29,433 --> 00:17:31,767
That's why you said that.

330
00:17:31,900 --> 00:17:34,600
But I know
you still have kindness in you.

331
00:17:34,733 --> 00:17:36,533
Can your conscience bear to know

332
00:17:36,667 --> 00:17:39,767
that our child is caught
in this feud?

333
00:17:39,900 --> 00:17:42,067
Uncle, have mercy on us.

334
00:17:42,200 --> 00:17:44,000
And on our baby.

335
00:17:44,133 --> 00:17:45,533
We didn't do anything wrong.

336
00:17:45,667 --> 00:17:48,633
We were just caught
in their feud.

337
00:17:49,767 --> 00:17:53,900
Please, tell us
where our baby is.

338
00:17:54,033 --> 00:17:55,333
What are you two doing?

339
00:17:55,467 --> 00:17:58,467
How is he going to help us
if you're going to beat him up?

340
00:17:58,600 --> 00:18:01,067
Aren't you furious about
what he said about our kids?

341
00:18:01,200 --> 00:18:02,300
- Our grandchild?
- Of course,

342
00:18:02,433 --> 00:18:04,367
it's not easy for me
to hear that.

343
00:18:04,500 --> 00:18:08,233
How do you think
Red and Eden feel?

344
00:18:08,367 --> 00:18:10,067
Look at how Red took it.

345
00:18:10,200 --> 00:18:12,033
Did he attack him? Beat him up?

346
00:18:12,167 --> 00:18:13,267
No, he did not! Because he knows

347
00:18:13,400 --> 00:18:16,233
it's not the way
to make Zandro talk.

348
00:18:18,033 --> 00:18:20,033
He's not going to tell us
anything.

349
00:18:20,167 --> 00:18:22,333
We're not going to get anything
from that bastard!

350
00:18:22,500 --> 00:18:23,867
That's why I hit him!

351
00:18:24,000 --> 00:18:25,500
That's enough.

352
00:18:25,633 --> 00:18:26,667
You two should stay here.

353
00:18:26,800 --> 00:18:28,400
We're going to talk to him.

354
00:18:28,533 --> 00:18:29,567
Stay here.

355
00:18:29,700 --> 00:18:30,867
Are you going back
to talk to him?

356
00:18:31,000 --> 00:18:32,500
Yes.

357
00:18:32,633 --> 00:18:33,767
He'll only make you upset.

358
00:18:35,067 --> 00:18:38,567
We still need to try
for our grandchild's sake.

359
00:18:38,700 --> 00:18:39,733
Lucho's right.

360
00:18:39,867 --> 00:18:41,700
We won't get any information
from him.

361
00:18:41,833 --> 00:18:43,667
That's why I'm going to try.

362
00:18:43,800 --> 00:18:45,067
Just stay here.

363
00:18:45,200 --> 00:18:46,167
Stay here.

364
00:18:50,700 --> 00:18:53,000
What can I get from helping you?

365
00:18:53,133 --> 00:18:54,700
All of you are out here,
having the time of your life.

366
00:18:54,867 --> 00:18:57,100
While I'm rotting in jail.

367
00:18:57,233 --> 00:18:59,433
Zandro, we'll help you
with your case.

368
00:19:02,533 --> 00:19:06,633
We'll get you a great lawyer
to lessen your punishment.

369
00:19:07,600 --> 00:19:10,133
Please, just tell us the truth.

370
00:19:24,400 --> 00:19:26,200
Rina planned
to make you hate each other.

371
00:19:28,100 --> 00:19:30,800
She sent you several threats

372
00:19:31,900 --> 00:19:33,533
and made it seem
like Amanda did it.

373
00:19:34,967 --> 00:19:36,333
No one died here.

374
00:19:36,467 --> 00:19:38,033
Sir, please sign here.

375
00:19:41,533 --> 00:19:42,600
No.

376
00:19:55,000 --> 00:19:56,300
We're not taking that!

377
00:19:59,933 --> 00:20:03,567
Do you mean the funeral flower,

378
00:20:03,733 --> 00:20:05,100
Yenyen's necklace,

379
00:20:06,233 --> 00:20:07,533
and the note...

380
00:20:07,667 --> 00:20:09,167
that's all my mom's doing?

381
00:20:12,267 --> 00:20:14,600
Even the bloody fetus?

382
00:20:16,200 --> 00:20:18,700
That's the reason
I had premature labor.

383
00:20:44,067 --> 00:20:45,267
Eden.

384
00:20:45,400 --> 00:20:46,733
What happened?

385
00:20:49,033 --> 00:20:50,033
- Auntie.
- What happened?

386
00:20:50,167 --> 00:20:51,133
Auntie!

387
00:20:52,633 --> 00:20:53,600
Oh my god!

388
00:20:54,767 --> 00:20:56,767
She did all that.

389
00:20:56,900 --> 00:20:59,133
We didn't know you'd go
into labor because of that.

390
00:21:00,267 --> 00:21:03,933
But we were prepared
for what could happen.

391
00:21:04,067 --> 00:21:06,333
You were ready
to take our child from us?

392
00:21:06,467 --> 00:21:09,267
So are you saying that my mom
is behind all of it?

393
00:21:09,433 --> 00:21:11,867
But why did you have
to get the child involved?

394
00:21:13,333 --> 00:21:14,933
I tried to talk her out of it.

395
00:21:16,333 --> 00:21:19,667
But she wanted to separate
Red and Eden.

396
00:21:21,233 --> 00:21:24,300
My sister hates you

397
00:21:24,433 --> 00:21:26,600
more than she cares
about her grandchild, Amanda.

398
00:21:27,700 --> 00:21:29,600
She still has Amanda's blood.

399
00:21:29,733 --> 00:21:33,167
Do you think I'll care
about that child?

400
00:21:33,300 --> 00:21:34,433
Never!

401
00:21:34,567 --> 00:21:35,867
What will happen
when she goes into labor?

402
00:21:36,000 --> 00:21:38,500
She'll give birth, yes.

403
00:21:38,633 --> 00:21:39,600
But...

404
00:21:40,700 --> 00:21:43,367
they won't bring a child home.

405
00:21:44,433 --> 00:21:45,567
Thank you.

406
00:21:47,233 --> 00:21:50,467
Let me know
if that's not enough.

407
00:21:50,600 --> 00:21:52,067
I can give you more.

408
00:21:52,200 --> 00:21:53,600
You're a midwife, right?

409
00:21:55,800 --> 00:21:57,233
I want a fetus.

410
00:21:58,267 --> 00:21:59,400
Can you give me one?

411
00:21:59,533 --> 00:22:01,567
What are you going to do
with it?

412
00:22:01,700 --> 00:22:03,733
Let's just say

413
00:22:03,867 --> 00:22:05,467
I'm going to give it as a gift.

414
00:22:07,533 --> 00:22:09,067
My future daughter-in-law.

415
00:22:10,533 --> 00:22:12,400
I can do that for you.

416
00:22:12,533 --> 00:22:15,433
We can talk about it.

417
00:22:15,600 --> 00:22:19,833
You won't have a problem with me
as long as the price is right.

418
00:22:19,967 --> 00:22:22,133
I have more jobs for you to do.

419
00:22:23,300 --> 00:22:26,567
Just make sure
I can count on you.

420
00:22:26,700 --> 00:22:28,433
No problem, Madam.

421
00:22:30,467 --> 00:22:33,767
The midwife

422
00:22:33,900 --> 00:22:36,067
that helped you give birth

423
00:22:36,200 --> 00:22:37,433
was working with us.

424
00:22:39,567 --> 00:22:43,533
We switched your baby
to a dead one.

425
00:22:44,667 --> 00:22:46,967
That's the baby you buried.

426
00:22:48,233 --> 00:22:50,167
So that means our baby's alive?

427
00:22:58,733 --> 00:23:00,033
Hello?

428
00:23:00,167 --> 00:23:01,067
Hello?

429
00:23:01,200 --> 00:23:02,533
Mom, where's our baby?

430
00:23:02,667 --> 00:23:03,867
Relax, Red.

431
00:23:04,000 --> 00:23:05,433
Don't get too excited.

432
00:23:05,567 --> 00:23:08,033
Please, don't hurt our baby!

433
00:23:08,167 --> 00:23:11,233
Well, you know
it's all up to you, Eden.

434
00:23:11,367 --> 00:23:13,300
I will give you
anything you want.

435
00:23:13,433 --> 00:23:14,400
Anything I want?

436
00:23:14,533 --> 00:23:15,500
Fine.

437
00:23:16,700 --> 00:23:20,633
I will give your baby back
if...

438
00:23:22,600 --> 00:23:26,433
you'll give me your mom.

439
00:23:27,467 --> 00:23:31,933
Give me Amanda
in exchange for your child.

440
00:23:32,067 --> 00:23:33,067
Deal?
